FBIS3-56424 "drsov011_b_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Reportedly Undecided LD1601221794 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 2020 GMT 16 Jan 94 LD1601221794 Moscow Russian Television Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The first reaction to Gaydar's resignation is quite contradictory. In the opinion of Sergey Zverev, who represents the Most group, Russia's major financial association, Deputy Prime Minister Boris Fedorov is the key figure in the implementation of financial and economic reforms. If he were to follow Gaydar, the situation would be seriously affected. Fedorov has not made up his mind yet about his resignation, though he does not rule out such a possibility. If Aleksandr Zaveryukha becomes deputy prime minister and I am offered just the post of minister, I will not join the Cabinet of Ministers, he told Interfax today. [passage omitted]
